reviewText:
The title is odd, but it's accurate. We've got a lot of cartoons here, a lot of which aren't starring the duck.

1. To Duck or Not to Duck? (1943, Jones; Daffy Duck and Elmer Fudd)
2. Birth of a Notion (1947, McKimson; Daffy)
3. Conrad the Sailor (1942, Jones; Daffy and Conrad Cat)
4. The Hep Cat (1942, Clampett)
5. The Dover Boys (1942, Jones)
6. House-Hunting Mice (1948, Jones; Hubie and Bertie)
7. Daffy Duck and the Dinosaur (1939, Jones)
